---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/mainlayout.astro";
import PageSection from "../components/PageSection.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Colophon | Alex Hordal" isHome={false}>
  <div class="page-grid page-grid-1300">
    <!-- Left Column -->
    <aside class="page-title-column">
      <h1>Colophon</h1>

      <p class="page-description">
        Learn about how this site was made.
      </p>

      
    </aside>

    <!-- Right Column -->
    <section class="page-content-column">
      <PageSection title={`<i class="fa-solid fa-book-open section-icon"></i> On The Front Cover`}>
      
<p>The image on the front page of this website is a grayscale representation of a map I created titled <a href="/projects/hawaii-seafloor-to-summit">Hawaiʻi:Seafloor to Summit</a>. The image shows the full vertical extent—from seafloor to summit—of a portion of the eight main Hawaiian Islands represented using a topobathymetric DEM and hillshading.</p>
      </PageSection>
  <PageSection title={`<i class="fa-solid fa-microchip section-icon"></i> Tech Stack`}>
      
<p>The website itself is built using <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a>, <a href="https://mdxjs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MDX</a>, <a href="https://vercel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Vercel</a>, <a href="https://github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>, and <a href="https://fontawesome.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Font Awesome</a>, with a strong emphasis on semantic and validated <a href="https://validator.w3.org/nu/?doc=https://www.alexhordal.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">HTML</a>, modern <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CSS</a> architecture, performant image delivery, structured long-form project documentation, and scalable content architecture for cartographic and GIS-focused work.</p>
      </PageSection>
      <PageSection title={`<i class="fa-solid fa-brain section-icon"></i> AI-Assisted Development`}>
      
<p>This website was developed through a combination of traditional frontend experimentation and iterative AI-assisted development. Generative AI was used throughout the project as a conversational tool for troubleshooting, refining layouts, exploring component architecture, and improving development workflows.</p>

<p>Rather than functioning as a simple code generator, the process involved ongoing back-and-forth iteration focused on maintainability, scalability, and editorial presentation. Many aspects of the site, including the content architecture, image handling pipeline, reusable Astro components, and project organization system, were developed incrementally through this collaborative workflow.</p>


      </PageSection>
       

    
    </section>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
